<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause author="Kieran O'Donnell" dateTime="2021-03-04T17:01:12" id="_9c3a4a92-8a34-4f28-ab20-2a38a7f1fbe2" outputclass="ncc-clause" type="insert"><meta><facet building="Class 2"/><facet building="Class 3"/><facet building="Class 4"/><facet building="Class 5"/><facet building="Class 6"/><facet building="Class 7a"/><facet building="Class 7b"/><facet building="Class 8"/><facet building="Class 9a"/><facet building="Class 9b"/><facet building="Class 9c"/><facet building="Class 10b"/><facet climate="Climate zone 8"/></meta><sptc>5.4.3</sptc><title id="_f4cd85c1-d8fa-42b3-8e75-eff3d45f2434">Internal walls</title><archive-num>New for 2022</archive-num><subclause id="_4e731774-4a5e-49a9-9aa8-86dac1b5f013" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_a2af50cf-fdf1-43c9-8608-26e1349d4914">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>Internal masonry walls must be engaged with other walls, must comply with the relevant provisions of this Part and must be—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_9ddddaf8-93af-49da-a4a5-a8c15a094171">not less than 75 mm thick; and</li><li id="_27018cc9-d5fc-4e37-9fc0-0463a4163ed7">supported by either—<ol><li id="_3568c2d8-7a91-449e-9275-89aba924f460">the ceiling structure in accordance with <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/4842_0.14.0.xml#_611072b0-c799-485e-8354-a774a1bc8ceb" id="_1d99abe2-e5c9-4246-ba5d-ba9b7a9f8964" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Figure 5.4.3a</xref>; or</li><li>return walls in accordance with <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/4843_0.15.0.xml#_bd1eb505-0bd3-43d2-9ddb-46b31626a459" id="_ed2bcef9-cc40-47b6-94fc-1e70c98c33fe" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Figure 5.4.3b</xref>.</li></ol></li></ol></subclause><image-reference author="Kieran O'Donnell" conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/4842_0.14.0.xml" dateTime="2021-03-04T14:53:27" id="_611072b0-c799-485e-8354-a774a1bc8ceb" type="insert"><num>5.4.3a</num><title id="_e59b5460-5717-4d60-9d30-aa40ddd42824">Support for internal walls—supported by ceiling structure</title><image alt="Support for internal walls—supported by ceiling structure" height="878" heightdpi="200" href="ERROR_IN_RESOLVING_URI:5-4-3a-support-for-internal-walls-supported-by-ceiling-structure.eps" width="1200" widthdpi="200"><image height="878" heightdpi="200" href="C:\Users\bkiem\AppData\Roaming\Quark\XML Author\Temp\media1_e2ed7967-9745-4991-abe0-620adb9b36e5.jpg" width="1200" widthdpi="200"/></image><desc-note id="_75a0a367-a780-409b-b148-58b1a01324aa"><ol outputclass="numbered"><li id="_1235f5eb-684a-4333-9efd-24e381dd6e25">Timber joist must be fixed to top plate in accordance with <xref format="dita" href="ERROR_IN_RESOLVING_URI:H1D6-framing.xml#_ce1f1e96-c16e-4d79-afbd-ae4e90289707" id="_e76a961f-93b6-45f5-83e4-c93dcb82d16a" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="subclause">H1D6(4)</xref>.</li><li id="_88ed1bb1-a388-4798-95f0-18e8603a06cc">Fixing of top plate to masonry wall must be in accordance with <xref format="dita" href="ERROR_IN_RESOLVING_URI:5-6-6-fixing-straps-and-tie-down-systems.xml#_a6e5c820-fb0b-492c-9798-51c8d108ef26" id="_685dba66-5992-4a44-b6bd-32ee5b83a08d" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="ncc-clause">5.6.6</xref>.</li></ol></desc-note></image-reference><image-reference author="Kieran O'Donnell" conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/4843_0.15.0.xml" dateTime="2021-03-04T14:53:46" id="_bd1eb505-0bd3-43d2-9ddb-46b31626a459" type="insert"><num>5.4.3b</num><title id="_10b139e3-abc0-4ce3-9aff-ca3a5aa7b59b">Support for internal walls—supported by return walls</title><image href="ERROR_IN_RESOLVING_URI:5-4-3b-support-for-internal-walls-supported-by-return-walls.eps"><image _resize_="false" href="C:\Users\bkiem\AppData\Roaming\Quark\XML Author\Temp\media1_2fae8b83-7597-410c-b968-73eacacdc537.tif" imagePlaceholder=""/></image><desc-note id="_52a9822f-4737-414f-9e34-d6a7a1a31a51"><ol outputclass="numbered"><li id="_638aff15-6d8b-4c2b-94cf-43e1cf6a2d44">An opening of not more than 600 mm x 900 mm is allowed to internal walls without additional support.</li><li id="_b363ff40-943b-4d23-bce1-2ce60c226a8e">Openings larger than as described in Note 1 and door openings must be supported.</li><li id="_9ad4fe93-4206-4435-9c44-cf01ce331362">The maximum allowable height for the wall is described in <xref format="dita" href="ERROR_IN_RESOLVING_URI:5-4-3a-support-for-internal-walls-supported-by-ceiling-structure.xml#_611072b0-c799-485e-8354-a774a1bc8ceb" id="_644ea5e0-915a-418d-b4f0-e729bad194f7" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Figure 5.4.3a</xref>.</li><li id="_ff82dd04-586f-4b11-8b35-9128b8fb69ed">Articulation joints must be in accordance with <xref format="dita" href="ERROR_IN_RESOLVING_URI:5-6-8-vertical-articulation-joints.xml#_b4f52947-629b-4c1b-a356-af9920e339b0" id="_c75a0503-3052-484a-ad00-f168d01da8d4" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="ncc-clause">5.6.8</xref>.</li></ol></desc-note></image-reference><callout id="_3585b409-f252-4c3c-ae97-b6e12e8e63f4"><callout-type ncc-info-type="info"/><p>A full height door frame or stud fastened at the roof framing and tied to the wall at 300 mm centres can be considered equivalent to a return wall.</p></callout></clause>